    "content": "# Custom Domains\n\nCustom domains allow you to use your own branded domain for shortened links instead of the default `bdg.et` domain. This helps maintain brand consistency and builds trust with your audience.\n\n## Benefits of Custom Domains\n\n- **Brand Recognition**: Use your own domain to reinforce your brand\n- **Trust**: Users are more likely to click links from recognized domains\n- **Analytics**: Better tracking and attribution for your campaigns\n- **Control**: Full control over your link structure and appearance\n\n## Requirements\n\nTo set up a custom domain, you'll need:\n\n1. **A domain name** that you own and control\n2. **DNS access** to configure DNS records\n3. **SSL certificate** (automatically provided by Badget)\n4. **Pro or Enterprise plan** (custom domains not available on free plan)\n\n## Setup Process\n\n### Step 1: Add Your Domain\n\n1. Navigate to **Settings** â†’ **Domains** in your Badget dashboard\n2. Click **\"Add Custom Domain\"**\n3. Enter your domain name (e.g., `short.yourcompany.com`)\n4. Click **\"Add Domain\"**\n\n### Step 2: Configure DNS\n\nAdd the following DNS records to your domain:\n\n#### For Subdomains (Recommended)\n\nIf using a subdomain like `short.yourcompany.com`:\n\n```\nType: CNAME\nName: short\nValue: cname.badget.app\nTTL: 3600\n```\n\n#### For Root Domains\n\nIf using a root domain like `yourcompany.co`:\n\n```\nType: A\nName: @\nValue: 76.76.19.123\nTTL: 3600\n\nType: A\nName: @\nValue: 76.76.21.123\nTTL: 3600\n```\n\n### Step 3: Verify Domain\n\n1. Return to your Badget dashboard\n2. Click **\"Verify Domain\"** next to your added domain\n3. Wait for DNS propagation (usually 5-60 minutes)\n4. Once verified, your domain status will show as \"Active\"\n\n### Step 4: Configure SSL\n\nSSL certificates are automatically provisioned and renewed by Badget. This process typically takes 5-10 minutes after domain verification.\n\n## Domain Configuration Options\n\n### Default Domain\n\nSet one of your custom domains as the default for new links:\n\n1. Go to **Settings** â†’ **Domains**\n2. Click the **\"Set as Default\"** button next to your preferred domain\n3. All new links will use this domain unless specified otherwise\n\n### Link-Specific Domains\n\nYou can choose which domain to use when creating individual links:\n\n```bash\ncurl -X POST https://api.badget.app/links \\\n  -H \"Authorization: Bearer YOUR_API_KEY\" \\\n  -d '{\n    \"url\": \"https://example.com\",\n    \"domain\": \"short.yourcompany.com\"\n  }'\n```\n\n## Best Practices\n\n### Subdomain Recommendations\n\n- `short.yourcompany.com`\n- `link.yourcompany.com` \n- `go.yourcompany.com`\n- `click.yourcompany.com`\n\n### DNS Considerations\n\n1. **TTL Settings**: Use lower TTL values (300-3600 seconds) for easier changes\n2. **CDN Compatibility**: Our CNAME works with most CDN providers\n3. **Backup Records**: Keep a record of your original DNS settings\n\n### Security\n\n- Always use HTTPS (automatically configured)\n- Monitor your domain for unauthorized use\n- Set up domain monitoring alerts\n- Review access logs regularly\n\n## Troubleshooting\n\n### Common Issues\n\n#### Domain Not Verifying\n\n1. **Check DNS Propagation**: Use tools like whatsmydns.net\n2. **Verify DNS Records**: Ensure exact match with provided values\n3. **Wait Longer**: DNS changes can take up to 24 hours\n4. **Contact Support**: If issues persist after 24 hours\n\n#### SSL Certificate Issues\n\n- SSL certificates are automatically managed\n- If you see SSL errors, wait 10-15 minutes and try again\n- For persistent issues, contact our support team\n\n#### Links Not Working\n\n1. **Verify Domain Status**: Check dashboard for \"Active\" status\n2. **Test DNS Resolution**: Use `nslookup` or `dig` commands\n3. **Clear Browser Cache**: Try in incognito/private mode\n4. **Check Firewall Settings**: Ensure ports 80 and 443 are open\n\n### DNS Commands for Verification\n\nCheck your DNS configuration:\n\n```bash\n# Check CNAME record\ndig short.yourcompany.com CNAME\n\n# Check A record\ndig yourcompany.co A\n\n# Verify SSL certificate\nopenssl s_client -connect short.yourcompany.com:443\n```\n\n## Migration from Other Services\n\n### From Bitly\n\n1. Export your existing links from Bitly\n2. Set up your custom domain in Badget\n3. Use our API to bulk import links\n4. Update any hardcoded references\n\n### From Other Providers\n\nWe provide migration tools and support for:\n\n- TinyURL\n- Short.io\n- Rebrandly\n- Custom solutions\n\nContact our migration team for assistance.\n\n## Enterprise Features\n\nEnterprise customers get additional domain features:\n\n- **Multiple Domains**: Unlimited custom domains\n- **Advanced Analytics**: Domain-specific analytics\n- **White-label Options**: Remove Badget branding\n- **Priority Support**: Dedicated domain setup assistance\n- **SLA Guarantees**: 99.9% uptime commitment\n\n## API Reference\n\n### Add Domain\n\n```bash\nPOST /domains\n{\n  \"domain\": \"short.yourcompany.com\"\n}\n```\n\n### List Domains\n\n```bash\nGET /domains\n```\n\n### Delete Domain\n\n```bash\nDELETE /domains/{domain}\n```\n\n## Support\n\nNeed help with custom domains?\n\n- **Documentation**: Check our detailed setup guides\n- **Live Chat**: Available 9 AM - 5 PM PST\n- **Email Support**: domains@badget.app\n- **Video Tutorials**: Available in our help center\n\nFor enterprise customers, dedicated domain specialists are available 24/7.",
